    <!-- 1. INTRODUCTION -->
    <h4 class="fw-bold">1. Introduction</h4>
    <p>
        The <b>Comprehensive Vocational Assessment Tool (CVAT)</b> is a digital system used to evaluate
        functional abilities, work skills, vocational aptitude, interests, and workplace behaviour of adults with
        intellectual disabilities. The portal digitizes assessment, review, reporting, comparison, and progress tracking.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- 2. PURPOSE -->
    <h4 class="fw-bold">2. Purpose & Utility</h4>
    <p>The tool is used for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Vocational skill assessment for adults aged 18+</li>
        <li>Training need identification</li>
        <li>Employability evaluation</li>
        <li>Career planning & job role mapping</li>
        <li>Recording long-term progress</li>
    </ul>

    <h5 class="fw-bold mt-3">When is it used?</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>During transition-to-work phase</li>
        <li>When designing individualized vocational training plans</li>
        <li>For placement decisions</li>
        <li>During periodic reviews</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />

